Per‑Mode Color‑Burst Tuning (Nano64 → Composite encoder)
Nano64’s BasicMachineNano64Color head produces digital RGB, which the composite encoder converts into:

NTSC: QAM colorburst

PAL: phase‑alternating QAM

SECAM: FM chroma

These presets tune the encoder so Nano64’s 16‑color palette stays stable.

NTSC
nano.colorburst_phase = 0.0
nano.colorburst_amplitude = 1.00
nano.chroma_bandwidth = 1.00
nano.luma_gain = 1.00
nano.pedestal = 7.5   # NTSC setup level

NTSC-J
nano.pedestal = 0.0
nano.colorburst_phase = 0.0
nano.colorburst_amplitude = 1.00

PAL
nano.colorburst_phase = ALTERNATE
nano.colorburst_amplitude = 0.90
nano.chroma_bandwidth = 0.85
nano.luma_gain = 1.05
nano.pedestal = 0.0

PAL60
nano.colorburst_phase = ALTERNATE
nano.colorburst_amplitude = 0.95
nano.chroma_bandwidth = 0.90

SECAM
nano.chroma_system = FM
nano.fm_deviation = 1.00
nano.luma_gain = 1.10
nano.chroma_bandwidth = 0.70

